{{page-title "Documentation — Browser Extension"}}
<div class="container mx-auto max-w-3xl py-6 px-4 space-y-6">

  <Panel::Card>
    <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-2">
      Career Caddy Sender
    </h1>
    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
      The Career Caddy Sender is a browser extension that captures any job
      posting you're looking at and sends it to your Career Caddy library with a
      single click. The page becomes a
      <LinkTo @route="docs.job-posts" class="text-accent-600 underline">Job Post</LinkTo>,
      optionally
      <LinkTo
        @route="docs.scores"
        class="text-accent-600 underline"
      >scored</LinkTo>
      against your
      <LinkTo @route="docs.career-data" class="text-accent-600 underline">Career
        Data</LinkTo>
      automatically.
    </p>
    <div>
      {{#if this.installLink.available}}
        <a
          href={{this.installLink.url}}
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-md bg-jade-600 px-5 py-2.5 text-sm font-semibold text-white shadow-sm hover:bg-jade-700"
        >
          <svg
            xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
            class="size-5 shrink-0"
            fill="none"
            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
            stroke-width="1.5"
            stroke="currentColor"
            aria-hidden="true"
          >
            <path
              stroke-linecap="round"
              stroke-linejoin="round"
              d="M12 10.5v6m3-3H9m4.06-7.19-2.12-2.12a1.5 1.5 0 0 0-1.061-.44H4.5A2.25 2.25 0 0 0 2.25 6v12a2.25 2.25 0 0 0 2.25 2.25h15A2.25 2.25 0 0 0 21.75 18V9a2.25 2.25 0 0 0-2.25-2.25h-5.379a1.5 1.5 0 0 1-1.06-.44Z"
            />
          </svg>
          {{this.installLink.label}}
        </a>
      {{else}}
        <div
          class="rounded-md border border-amber-300 bg-amber-50 p-4 text-sm text-amber-900"
        >
          <p class="font-semibold mb-1">{{this.installLink.label}}</p>
          <p>
            The extension is published for Chrome (also Edge, Brave, Opera) and
            Firefox. Open this page in one of those browsers to get the install
            button.
          </p>
        </div>
      {{/if}}
      <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-2">
        Available on the Chrome Web Store and Firefox Add-ons. We pick the right
        store automatically based on the browser you're viewing this page in.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Panel::Card>

  <Panel::Card>
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">First-time setup</h2>
    <ol class="space-y-3 text-gray-600 list-decimal list-inside">
      <li>
        Install the extension from the store, then pin the toolbar icon (in
        Chrome it lives behind the puzzle-piece menu until you pin it).
      </li>
      <li>
        Make sure you're signed in to
        <code class="text-sm">careercaddy.online</code>
        in another tab — the extension uses your existing SPA session, so
        there's no second login.
      </li>
      <li>
        Click the toolbar icon. The first time, the popup shows a
        <strong>Connect</strong>
        button. Click it. The extension reads your session, mints a dedicated
        API key (named
        <code class="text-sm">Career Caddy Sender — YYYY-MM-DD</code>), and
        stores only that key locally.
      </li>
    </ol>
    <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm mt-3">
      If you're not signed in, the popup will link you to the login page — sign
      in there, reopen the popup, and you're connected.
    </p>
  </Panel::Card>

  <Panel::Card>
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">Sending a job post</h2>
    <ol class="space-y-3 text-gray-600 list-decimal list-inside">
      <li>
        Open any job posting in a normal tab.
      </li>
      <li>
        Click the Career Caddy toolbar icon. The popup reads the URL of the
        active tab and asks the API whether you've already saved this post.
      </li>
      <li>
        If it's new, you'll see
        <strong>Send this page</strong>
        — click it. The extension reads the page text, POSTs it to your account,
        and the popup closes.
      </li>
      <li>
        A system notification fires when the scrape finishes (typically in ~30
        seconds). You'll get
        <em>Added ✓ — &lt;Title&gt;</em>
        when the JobPost is created.
      </li>
    </ol>
  </Panel::Card>

  <Panel::Card>
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">
      Auto-score against Career Data
    </h2>
    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-3">
      The popup has a toggle for
      <strong>"Also score against career data"</strong>. When it's on, the
      extension chains a
      <LinkTo
        @route="docs.scores"
        class="text-accent-600 underline"
      >Score</LinkTo>
      generation onto the scrape and the OS notification reports the result
      (e.g.
      <em>Scored 87 ✓ — &lt;Title&gt;</em>) instead of just confirming the add.
      If scoring fails (no Career Data set up yet, AI quota exhausted), it falls
      back to the plain "Added" notification so you still hear something.
    </p>
    <p class="text-gray-600">
      The toggle remembers its state. Defaults to on for fresh installs.
    </p>
  </Panel::Card>

  <Panel::Card>
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">
      Already-saved posts
    </h2>
    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-3">
      If the page you're on is already in your library, the popup says so and
      offers a link straight to the existing JobPost — no duplicate created.
    </p>
    <p class="text-gray-600">
      If the existing post is flagged
      <em>incomplete</em>
      (e.g. it was created from an email stub or the AI couldn't extract a job
      description from the original page), the popup heading swaps to
      <strong>Complete this post</strong>
      and the action button becomes
      <strong>Resend to complete</strong>. Clicking it re-sends the page text,
      which the API uses to fill in the missing fields without creating a
      duplicate.
    </p>
  </Panel::Card>

  <Panel::Card>
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">Disconnecting</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-600">
      Click
      <strong>Disconnect</strong>
      in the popup to revoke the extension's API key on the server and clear it
      from local storage. You can also revoke the key by name under
      <em>Settings → API Keys</em>
      in Career Caddy. Either way, the extension goes back to its first-run
      Connect screen the next time you open it.
    </p>
  </Panel::Card>

  <Panel::Card>
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">
      What it doesn't do
    </h2>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-600 list-disc list-inside">
      <li>It doesn't read any page until you click the toolbar icon.</li>
      <li>It doesn't track which sites you visit.</li>
      <li>It doesn't talk to anyone except your Career Caddy account.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-gray-600 mt-3">
      The full
      <LinkTo @route="docs.extension-privacy" class="text-accent-600 underline">
        privacy policy
      </LinkTo>
      walks through every permission the extension requests and why.
    </p>
  </Panel::Card>

</div>